I have just posted a new binary installer for Cantera for Windows.  It 
is file Cantera154c.msi.

This version improves translation of Chemkin-format reaction mechanism 
files.  It should now successfully convert any valid Chemkin-II 
mechanism.  (If you have one it fails on, please send it to me along 
with details of how you were converting it.)

If you installed Cantera from the workshop CD,  you should upgrade as 
soon as possible, since that version (but not prior net versions) had a 
bug that kept Chemkin file translation from working at all.

The source distributions have not been updated yet, but of course the 
source code is always available by CVS.
Please let me know if there are any problems with this installer.

Dave
